jsl.modeling.elements.queue
Class QObject

java.lang.Object
  jsl.modeling.elements.queue.QObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<QObject>, GetValueIfc, IdentityIfc
Direct Known Subclasses:
Entity
public class QObject
extends Object
implements IdentityIfc, Comparable<QObject>, GetValueIfc

QObject can be used as a base class for objects that need to be placed in queues on a regular basis. In addition, a QObject is created each time that an arbitrary object is placed in a Queue. A QObject "wraps" the arbitrary object, so that statistics can be collected on arbitrary objects placed in Queues. A QObject can be in one and only one Queue at a time. An arbitrary object (not subclassed from QObject) can be placed in multiple Queues because a new QObject is used each time the object is placed in a Queue. If a QObject is placed in a Queue no wrapping QObject is created, thereby saving an additional object creation (with the restriction that it can be in only one Queue at a time).

setPriority

public final void setPriority(int priority)
Sets the priority to the supplied value If the QObject is queued, the queue's changePriority() method is called (possibly causing a reordering of the queue) which may cause significant reordering overhead otherwise the priority is directly changed Changing this value only changes how the QObjects are compared and may or may not change how they are ordered in the queue, depending on the queue discipline used

priority - An integer representing the priority of the QObject
